# Example trusted keys file for store_service
#
# V-007 Phase 5: Production signature validation
#
# This file contains Ed25519 public keys that are trusted to sign artifacts.
# Each line should contain a base64-encoded Ed25519 public key (32 bytes).
#
# Format:
#   - Lines starting with # are comments (ignored)
#   - Empty lines are ignored
#   - Each non-comment line must be a base64-encoded Ed25519 public key
#
# Usage:
#   1. Generate a keypair:
#      cargo run --example generate_ed25519_keypair
#
#   2. Add the PUBLIC KEY (base64) to this file
#
#   3. Set environment variable:
#      export RAMEN_STORE_TRUSTED_KEYS=/path/to/trusted_keys
#
#   4. Start store_service:
#      It will load trusted keys and enforce RequireSignature policy
#
# Security Notes:
#   - Keep PRIVATE KEYS secret and offline
#   - Only add public keys to this file
#   - Use one key per signer (build system, release manager, etc.)
#   - Rotate keys periodically (document rotation procedure)
#   - Use strong key generation (Ed25519, cryptographically secure random)
#
# Example (DO NOT USE IN PRODUCTION - these are placeholder keys):
# x0EJNLqqx4xFYWbqbMxKPex5Lvy5Y3jxGVjHfPbUQHY=

# Production keys (add your actual keys below):
# <PASTE_BASE64_PUBLIC_KEY_HERE>

# Backup signing key (optional):
# <PASTE_BACKUP_PUBLIC_KEY_HERE>

# Build system signing key (optional):
# <PASTE_BUILD_SYSTEM_PUBLIC_KEY_HERE>
